<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-149-346  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 149 346.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Personal Computing  April 1989 v13 n4 p107(8).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>What's new in color printers and plotters. (includes relatedarticle on plotters in CAD applications and an article on thedevelopment of color laser printers)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Honan, Patrick.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>New color dot-matrix, ink-jet and thermal printers are easier touse, offer richer colors, and are faster than earlier models.andP;  Inaddition, software support for color printers is becomingincreasingly available.andP;  Color printers are now able to printletters and other standard correspondence in addition to chartsand drawings.andP;  Color dot-matrix printers differ from non-colorprinters only in terms of ribbon and print-head, and remain thebest solution for general-purpose printing, but ink-jet andthermal printers are superior for business presentations.andP;  Ink-jetprinters can clog, however, and those with separate cartridges foreach color are preferable to those with all colors in a singlecartridge if one color is to be used predominantly.andP;  Thermalprinters are the best choice for high-quality output, andimprovements in controllers will yield a 50 to 100 percent gain inprocessing speed.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     PlottersColorNon-Impact PrintersInk-Jet PrintersThermal PrintersDot-Matrix Printers.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotographtable.andO;Caption:   Color printer and plotter companies. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>